commitResults.messageTitle: Renamed Chatbot, implemented skeletal startup & shutdown sequence
Added basic main loop logic to echo user input and exit upon the input "bye", added comments to all methods
Added logic for "add" and "list" commands, minor wording changes in some comments
Added logic for "done", "undo" and "toggle" commands to change task status
Expanded generic "add" command logic into subtypes "todo", "deadline" and "event" commands
Changed task.getStatusMsg() to pull from method getter instead of field
Fixed listTask() to properly align index spacing
Created somewhat-comprehensive test case and performed semi-auto UI testing
Fixed arg check logic, changed UTF Task icons to text, temporarily standardised error responses due to implementation oversights (bugfixes from UI testing)
Added error handling using Exceptions, restored more specific error messages
Added deletion of tasks, added behaviour for empty tasklist, minor comment/bot response fixes, added missing test cases for task completion
Reformat code minimally to facilitate implementation of features
commitResults.messageBody:
Current code is full of static abuse, impeding future implementation
which must follow coding conventions (e.g. OOP instance-passing).
Incidentally, proper code cleanup is scheduled for the near future.

Thus, perform the minimal amount of code cleanup.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add storage system to allow task data to persist between NotJippity sessions
Merge branch 'branch-Level-7'
Add DateTime recognition and listing of tasks associated to a date
commitResults.messageBody:
Change format of dates in tasks from String to DateTime for flexibility
and utility (e.g. ease of comparing dates).

Add a --date flag to "list" command to filter only tasks which are
associated with the given date (e.g. Deadline on that date, or Event
where given date falls within its From-To range).

Bugfix where Event uses the datafile's fromDateTime for its toDateTime.

Minor gitignore addition to ignore data files from local testing.
